	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - An off-duty police officer shot dead two
people and wounded another in Meadowlands, Johannesburg, before turning the gun
on himself, Gauteng police said on Tuesday. "He shot and killed his girlfriend, the girl's
mother, and also injured a tenant," said spokesperson Mack Mngomezulu. "After that he shot himself and died on the
scene." The incident happened at the constable's girlfriend's
house in Zone Eight around 18:00 on Monday. All three died on the scene. The tenant was taken to hospital. The constable's official firearm was found on the scene. "The motive is unknown. Police are investigating
murder, attempted murder, and an inquest case was opened," said
Mngomezulu.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  